    <item>
      <title>METU-NCC courses</title>
      <link>https://dorukalp.github.io/post/courses/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 14 Feb 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://dorukalp.github.io/post/courses/</guid>
      <description>&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Introduction to Fluid Mechanics, Must course, Spring semesters since 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drilling Engineering I, Must course, Fall semesters since 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Drilling Engineering II, Must course, Spring 2017.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Petroleum Engineering Project Design I, Must course, Fall semesters since 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enhanced Oil Recovery, Elective course, Spring semesters since 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mathematical Modeling of Hydrocarbon Reservoirs, Elective course, Fall semesters since 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Special Topics: Surface Operations, Elective course, Spring semesters 2018, 2019.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I developed this course as a new technical elective for the program. Course covers thermal-hydraulic calculations for single phase (liquid or gas) and two-phase flow (homogeneous model and Beggs &amp;amp; Brill correlation) in surface pipes, solution of pipe networks, phase equilibrium of hydrocarbon mixtures at the separator; and design of separator dimensions for physical separation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;8&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Petroleum Engineering Project Design II, Must course, Spring 2020.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
